            <h2>Education:<br /></h2>
<p>Business graduate degree from Norwegian School of Management BI <br />Degree in administrative law, Volda University College <br />Degree in information counselling, Lillehammer University College</p>
<h2>Professional experience:</h2>
<p>1995 – 2005 Mayor, municipality of Gran<br />1992-1996 Norwegian Labour Party, elected secretary for women’s issues <br />1985-1992 Department manager, Aas Data ICT firm<br />1978-1985 Hertz Car Rental. Finance and administration manager for 3 years </p>
<h2>Political career:</h2>
<p>2009&nbsp;&nbsp; Member of Parliament for Oppland county <br />2005 - 2009 State Secretary in the Ministry of Health and Care Services <br />1999 - 2005 Board chairman, Hadeland Energy Company<br />1996 -1999&nbsp; Board member, Hadeland Energy Company<br />1996 - 2005 Board member, Norwegian Association of Local and Regional Authorities (KS), Oppland county<br />1996 - 2005 Board member, Gjøvik University College<br />1983 -1991&nbsp; Municipal council member, Gran, school board member 1983-87, administrative council chairman 1987-1991<br />1987 -1991 Board member, Vestoppland Folk High School<br />1992 -1998 Representative of the Norwegian Labour party in international cooperation committees </p>
<h2>Other:</h2>
<p>1998 Member, Norway’s delegation to the UN General Assembly<br />Active as sports administrator/trainer and in political organisational work<br /></p>
